
Algorithm: Find Maximum Value in an Array using Bubble Sort
Start.

Define the function max_value(arrays):

Input: An array of numbers, arrays.
Output: The maximum value in the array.
Inside max_value function:

Initialize length as the size of the input array (arrays).
Loop i from 0 to length - 2 (outer loop for multiple passes):
Loop j from 0 to length - i - 2 (inner loop for comparing adjacent elements):
If arrays[j] > arrays[j + 1]:
Swap arrays[j] and arrays[j + 1].
After sorting, the largest value will be at the last index (arrays[length - 1]).
Return the largest value (maxValue).
Define the main() function:

Initialize the array scores = [60, 50, 95, 80, 70].
Call max_value(scores) to get the maximum value and store it in maxValue.
Print the value of maxValue.
Check if the program is being run directly:

If true, call the main() function.
End.
